data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async; in EF Core 11 that opt-in is gone. Every synchronous call **always throws** — no workaround, no flag.

All four of your methods are affected:

| Breaks | Fix |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First(...)` | `await FirstAsync(...)` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

Your repository must go fully async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple up — every caller of these methods must also become `async`/`await`. There is no opt-in to restore the old sync behavior.
